nodes.title: Model Sampling Flux Infos
widgets_values:
How the ModelSamplingFlux Parameters Work Together:

Max Shift sets the possible maximum flexibility. Standard 1.15
Base Shift sets the starting flexibility. Standard 0.50

Summary:
High Shift: More potential for adding new details and sharpness, but with an increased risk of noise and artifacts.
Low Shift: More controlled and potentially cleaner images with less risk of noise, but possibly less detail and sharpness.

nodes.title: !! Important Info!!
widgets_values:
If several variants are enabled, the lowest one is used.

If no extra image is enabled, the image from the load image group is used.

Standard:
The strength is controlled via the influence reduction, between 0.01 and 0.2 are good values

Mix prompt: 
Standard must be enabled, the strength is controlled via the influence 
reduction, between 0.01 and 0.5

Mix Recommended:
Redux  Conditioning Start 0
                    End 0.01 to 0.3
Prompt Conditioning Start 0 to 0.3
                    End 1

Redux advanced: 
Standard and mix prompt should be disabled

Mask only works with Redux Advanced!

If mask is enabled but no mask has been defined, Redux advanced cannot work!
